user.biography: Host of cooking show. Wife of cowboy. Mother of four...I mean five! ❤️ Designer of dishes. Butter is my boyfriend. Amen.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Ree Drummond - Pioneer Woman on September 17, 2021 tagging @brycedrummond. May be a closeup of 1 person, child, standing and outdoors.

node.text: Happy birthday to my third child and first son Bryce, who was my only anesthesia-free childbirth experience, who will eternally (to me) look like this first photo, and who will forever inhabit a very special portion of my heart—the portion devoted to mysterious minds and deep dimples. I love you, B-Man. So very, very much.

node.text: I may be the worst unboxer of all time, but at least I’m excited about my new cookbook! 🤓 “Super Easy” will be here October 19, and it’s full of dellllllicious recipes! ❤️ Available for preorder if you’d like it to be delivered on launch day while you’re still in your PJ’s. 😊

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ree Drummond - Pioneer Woman on September 11, 2021. May be an image of skyscraper and monument.

node.text: None of us will ever, ever forget the details of that day...where we were, who we were with, and the despair we felt as the realities of the terror attacks unfolded before our eyes. I remember it like it was yesterday. I also remember the way America came together in a common anger and grief. I pray for comfort for everyone who lost a child, a sibling, a parent, a partner, a friend, or any loved one on September 11, 2001. I can't imagine carrying that pain all these years, and I'm holding them in my heart today.💔

node.text: If I ever come over to your house and you can’t find me for awhile, just look for your dogs. Dogs are my favorite people! No offense to all my family and friends. Okay bye! 🐶 🐩 🐕

node.text: Find a friend who extends her trip an extra night so she and her fella can not only come to your kid’s Friday night football game (wearing team shirts they procured themselves btw 😭), but stay till the very end despite a thirty point lead. Joy the Baker is a good one. (And her fella is, too.❤️)

node.text: What would I do without my sister? Don’t know, don’t want to know. ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Ree Drummond - Pioneer Woman on August 27, 2021 tagging @joythebaker. May be an image of 1 person, standing and grass.

node.text: Joy the Baker and I go way back (in food blogging years!) and the rare times we get to see each other are always concentrated and so special to me. We laugh and laugh, and I don’t know…she’s just a treasure to be around and I’m so glad we met so many years ago. My sister Betsy is here now too, so she got to join in our fun…and poor Will (Joy’s man ❤️) was outnumbered and we talked his ear off. And kinda grilled him a little 😊 but that’s what friends are for! Love you Joy!!

node.text: Oh, hi! This is me filming my first scene in an upcoming Christmas movie.🎄 Look at those tightly locked knees—I was certain I was gonna wind up fainting like those bridesmaids/groomsmen we used to see fall over on America’s Funniest Home Videos. Anyway, yeah—I was nervous filming this movie, because I am not an actor and being on a movie set in Utah was a whole different experience than filming a cooking show in my own kitchen. Fortunately, once a woman hits her fifties, the possibility of embarrassing herself really doesn’t keep her from doing anything in life. 😂 Anyway, here are some behind the scenes shots of my first (and probably last!!!) acting gig. “Candy Coated Christmas” is coming in November! (By the way, my knees are locked in every single one of these photos, I just noticed. I might need a cortisone shot after all that stress on my cartilage. Things I never said when I was younger…🤓)

node.text: It may still be 2,763 degrees outside, but that doesn’t mean we can’t get excited for fall! The new issue of PW Magazine is on newsstands now, and look! My little pumpkin is holding a little pumpkin. 🤓 Happiness is hanging with Paige, and happiness is cooler weather…and all the food and fun (and football) that comes with it! ❤️

node.text: 2 trips 2 hours apart to 2 different Walmart locations plus 2 hours of organizing and 2 iced coffees was all it took to get Bryce’s kitchen all set up and stocked yesterday. (Oh, and a 500 mile drive to Texas and back.) I guess it’s that important to me for my child to be able to make an egg. 😂 I love you, my son!
